>>2c0a802a-886b-4a6d-a49d-81a1062c39b1
>why would I have to install an update for the site manually? Isn't the whole point of zeronet that people send each other new changes on the website?

Because:

A. Some of us did a manual edit to the site code to test the Millchan codebace.

B. Just how your browser cache can muck up site updates, even when it is not meant to serve old code from cache, ZeroNet zite cache has the same problem.

Hitting check files makes znet interrogate it's cache copy against the main branch, and then cleans up the inconsistencys.
